---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — JWM" activePage="about">

  <div class="page-hero grid-overlay">
    <div class="hero-left">
      <p class="eyebrow">The person behind the frameworks</p>
      <h1 class="hero-name">John<br><em>Muhlenberg</em></h1>
      <p class="hero-role">Sales Engineer · Recharge · Denver, CO</p>
      <p class="hero-lede">I grew up just outside DC, moved west, and ended up building a career at the intersection of <strong>technical depth and commercial instinct</strong> — which turns out to be exactly where the most interesting problems live.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="avatar-frame">
        <img src="/john.png" alt="John Muhlenberg" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Origin story -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label mono-label">Origin story</p>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">I'll be upfront: my path to sales engineering is not a straight line. I graduated with a degree in <strong>Business Management</strong> and spent the first few years of my career figuring out what I actually wanted — which required trying a lot of things that weren't it.</p>
      <p class="prose">I started out reselling software to the government. Moved into <strong>technical recruiting</strong>, where I spent enough time inside engineering orgs to realize I wanted to be contributing to the industry, not just placing people in it. That restlessness eventually won. I stepped off the treadmill entirely, headed to <strong>Beaver Creek</strong> for a year, and spent a ski season working as a lift operator and mechanic — probably the best clarity I've ever bought.</p>
      <div class="pull-quote">"A year fixing chairlifts in Colorado turned out to be the most useful career move I ever made."</div>
      <p class="prose">I came back with a clearer sense of direction and landed a <strong>support engineer role</strong> at a small point-of-sale company. When that environment wasn't the right fit, I left — and spent time working with a friend on a <strong>commercial interior construction</strong> project management operation. It sharpened skills I still use daily: scoping complex projects, managing stakeholder expectations, and staying organized under pressure.</p>
      <p class="prose">Then I got married, COVID hit, and the world paused. I used that pause deliberately — completed a <strong>software engineering bootcamp</strong> to sharpen my technical foundations and re-entered the job market with a cleaner story to tell.</p>

      <div class="career-timeline">
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Government software</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Software reseller</p>
            <p class="career-note">First exposure to enterprise sales cycles and procurement complexity.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Recruiting</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Technical recruiter</p>
            <p class="career-note">Spent enough time inside engineering teams to realize I wanted to be building, not placing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Sabbatical</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Lift operator &amp; mechanic, Beaver Creek</p>
            <p class="career-note">A deliberate reset. Traded career momentum for altitude, clarity, and the satisfaction of fixing things with your hands.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Point of sale</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Support engineer</p>
            <p class="career-note">First real technical role. Learned that environment matters as much as the work itself.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Construction PM</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Project manager, commercial interiors</p>
            <p class="career-note">Outside tech but inside complexity. Sharpened stakeholder management, scoping, and keeping complicated projects moving.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item">
          <span class="career-role">Bootcamp · COVID</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Software engineering bootcamp</p>
            <p class="career-note">Used the forced pause to freshen up technical skills and re-enter the industry with sharper fundamentals.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="career-item career-item--accent">
          <span class="career-role">Recharge</span>
          <div class="career-detail">
            <p class="career-title">Support Engineer → Implementation Engineer → Sales Engineer</p>
            <p class="career-note">Joined in support, leveraged project management instincts into implementation, sought out cross-functional exposure, and found my way into SE — the first role where everything I'd done before finally made sense together.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="prose">The through-line, looking back, is that every detour taught me something the straight path wouldn't have. Sales engineering is the first role where all of it has been useful at once.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Values -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label mono-label">What I care about</p>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">A few principles that show up consistently in how I work.</p>
      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value-card">
          <p class="value-title">Honesty over comfort</p>
          <p class="value-desc">If a solution isn't the right fit, I'll say so. Short-term discomfort beats a bad implementation every time.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <p class="value-title">Clarity as a skill</p>
          <p class="value-desc">Technical depth is only useful if it can be communicated. I work hard at making complex things simple without making them wrong.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <p class="value-title">Build for the next engineer</p>
          <p class="value-desc">Whatever I design should be understandable by the person who inherits it — not just the person who built it. Ego-free architecture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="value-card">
          <p class="value-title">Curiosity over credentials</p>
          <p class="value-desc">I'd rather work with someone who asks great questions than someone who already has all the answers.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Outside of work -->
  <div class="section">
    <p class="section-label mono-label">Outside of work</p>
    <div class="section-body">
      <p class="prose">I grew up in <strong>northern Virginia</strong>, about 30 miles outside DC — close enough to absorb the city's energy, far enough to spend weekends in the Blue Ridge. The East Coast will always feel like home.</p>

      <p class="subsection-label">Sports</p>
      <p class="prose">Finding the right sport took trial and error. T-ball, soccer — the usual childhood attempts. Nothing stuck until I convinced my parents to let me try <strong>roller hockey</strong>. I picked it up quickly enough to be invited to try out for the <strong>USA Juniors inline hockey team</strong> — but pivoted to ice hockey instead, which reset the learning curve almost entirely. I worked up from house league to travel hockey and competed against junior-level teams. In high school I picked up <strong>lacrosse</strong> — the edge work and hand-eye coordination transferred from hockey faster than expected. In total: hockey for roughly <strong>15 years</strong>, lacrosse for <strong>8</strong>.</p>

      <div class="sport-timeline">
        <div class="sport-item">
          <span class="sport-label">Early years</span>
          <div class="sport-detail">
            <p class="sport-title">T-ball, soccer, experimenting</p>
            <p class="sport-note">The standard youth sports circuit. Nothing wrong with any of it — just not the thing that clicked.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sport-item">
          <span class="sport-label">Roller hockey</span>
          <div class="sport-detail">
            <p class="sport-title">The gateway sport</p>
            <p class="sport-note">Lower barrier to entry, faster skill development than expected. Invited to try out for USA Juniors inline — chose to pivot to ice instead.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sport-item">
          <span class="sport-label">Ice hockey · 15 yrs</span>
          <div class="sport-detail">
            <p class="sport-title">House league → travel → junior-level competition</p>
            <p class="sport-note">Started from scratch on ice and worked up through every level. The most formative athletic experience I've had.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sport-item">
          <span class="sport-label">Lacrosse · 8 yrs</span>
          <div class="sport-detail">
            <p class="sport-title">High school pickup, fast progression</p>
            <p class="sport-note">The hockey skill transfer was immediate — edge work, spatial awareness, hand-eye. Picked it up faster than almost anything else I've tried.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="sport-item sport-item--accent">
          <span class="sport-label">Snowboarding · 20 yrs</span>
          <div class="sport-detail">
            <p class="sport-title">Started skiing, never looked back</p>
            <p class="sport-note">The switch made sense: all my friends were boarding, and the mechanics mapped directly onto ice skating. Targeting 10+ days a season. Adult hockey and lacrosse leagues are on the horizon.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="subsection-label">City dating</p>
      <p class="prose">My wife and I got married in <strong>January 2020</strong>, abandoned our honeymoon when COVID shut everything down, moved in with her parents, and decided to turn the uncertainty into an experiment — find out where we actually want to be, city by city.</p>

      <div class="city-timeline">
        <div class="city-item">
          <span class="city-name">Chicago</span>
          <p class="city-note">Great architecture, brutal winters. Confirmed we need proximity to nature more than proximity to a skyline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="city-item">
          <span class="city-name">Denver</span>
          <p class="city-note">First time through — mountains within reach, dry air, a city that moves at a pace we liked. Filed away for later.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="city-item">
          <span class="city-name">New Orleans</span>
          <p class="city-note">Unmatched culture and food. Also confirmed that humidity is a dealbreaker.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="city-item">
          <span class="city-name">Charleston</span>
          <p class="city-note">Beautiful, unhurried, close to the coast. The East Coast pull was real — but the mountains kept calling louder.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="city-item city-item--accent">
          <span class="city-name">Denver (again)</span>
          <p class="city-note">We came back. The Rockies, the dry climate, the access to everything outdoors — it won. For now, at least.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="subsection-label">Reading, travel &amp; music</p>

      <div class="two-col">
        <div class="info-card">
          <p class="info-card-label mono-label">Reading</p>
          <p class="info-card-content">Fiction and nonfiction in equal measure — <strong>biographies, self-help, creativity, epic poems, sci-fi, thriller, mystery, historical fiction,</strong> and historical nonfiction. I want to finish a book knowing something I didn't before, or having felt something I wasn't expecting.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="info-card">
          <p class="info-card-label mono-label">Travel</p>
          <p class="info-card-content">Favorite countries so far: <strong>Sweden, Denmark, Germany, Spain.</strong> Up next: Japan, hopefully later this year. I travel looking for the thing a place does that nowhere else does quite the same way.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="prose">Music is where I'll lose people if they're not careful. I grew up in the <strong>Warped Tour era</strong> — emo, pop punk, punk, alternative rock, post-hardcore, hardcore, metal, and indie are the foundation. These days the range has expanded: jazz, blues, experimental, drum and bass, dubstep, bass house, and most of the broader EDM spectrum. Everything except country. Everything except riddim.</p>

      <div class="tag-group">
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag-row-label mono-label">Roots</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Emo</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Pop punk</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Post-hardcore</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Punk</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Alt rock</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Hardcore</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Metal</span>
          <span class="tag tag--accent">Indie</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag-row-label mono-label">Now</span>
          <span class="tag">Jazz</span>
          <span class="tag">Blues</span>
          <span class="tag">Experimental</span>
          <span class="tag">Drum &amp; bass</span>
          <span class="tag">Dubstep</span>
          <span class="tag">Bass house</span>
          <span class="tag">EDM</span>
        </div>
        <div class="tag-row">
          <span class="tag-row-label mono-label">Hard pass</span>
          <span class="tag tag--muted">Country</span>
          <span class="tag tag--muted">Riddim</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Connect -->
  <div class="connect-section">
    <div>
      <h2 class="connect-heading">Let's find something<br><em>worth talking about.</em></h2>
      <p class="connect-sub">Whether you want to talk subscription architecture, debate business strategy, or just swap book recommendations — I'm genuinely easy to reach.</p>
      <a href="mailto:jmuhlenberg16@yahoo.com" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top: 1.5rem; display: inline-block;">Send me a note</a>
    </div>
    <div class="connect-links">
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/jwmuhlenberg/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="connect-link">LinkedIn ↗</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/jmuhlenberg" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="connect-link">GitHub ↗</a>
      <a href="mailto:jmuhlenberg16@yahoo.com" class="connect-link">Email ↗</a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* Hero */
  .page-hero {
    padding: 10rem 3rem 0;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 340px;
    gap: 6rem; align-items: end;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .hero-left { padding-bottom: 5rem; }
  .hero-name { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem); line-height: 1.0; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .hero-name em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .hero-role { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .hero-lede { font-size: 1.15rem; font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--text-secondary); max-width: 560px; }
  .hero-lede strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 400; }

  .hero-right { align-self: end; }
  .avatar-frame {
    width: 100%; aspect-ratio: 3/4;
    background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    position: relative; overflow: hidden;
  }
  .avatar-initials { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 5rem; color: rgba(200,240,84,0.15); letter-spacing: -0.04em; user-select: none; }
  .avatar-grid { position: absolute; inset: 0; background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px), linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.03) 1px, transparent 1px); background-size: 30px 30px; }
  .avatar-caption { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-top: 1rem; text-align: right; }

  /* Sections */
  .section {
    padding: 5rem 3rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 5rem; align-items: start;
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
  }
  .section-label { padding-top: 0.35rem; position: sticky; top: 7rem; }
  .section-body { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.75rem; }

  .subsection-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent); margin-bottom: -0.5rem;
  }

  /* Career timeline */
  .career-timeline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .career-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); transition: background 0.2s; }
  .career-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .career-item:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .career-item--accent { background: rgba(200,240,84,0.03); }
  .career-role { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.64rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); padding: 1.35rem 1.5rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: flex-start; line-height: 1.5; }
  .career-item--accent .career-role { color: var(--accent); }
  .career-detail { padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; }
  .career-title { font-size: 0.86rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .career-note { font-size: 0.78rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  /* Values */
  .values-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .value-card { background: var(--surface); padding: 1.75rem; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .value-card:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .value-title { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .value-title::before { content: '—'; color: var(--accent); margin-right: 0.5rem; }
  .value-desc { font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  /* Sport timeline */
  .sport-timeline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .sport-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 180px 1fr; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); transition: background 0.2s; }
  .sport-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .sport-item:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .sport-item--accent { background: rgba(200,240,84,0.03); }
  .sport-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.64rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: flex-start; padding-top: 1.35rem; line-height: 1.5; }
  .sport-item--accent .sport-label { color: var(--accent); }
  .sport-detail { padding: 1.2rem 1.5rem; }
  .sport-title { font-size: 0.86rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.3rem; }
  .sport-note { font-size: 0.78rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); }

  /* City timeline */
  .city-timeline { display: flex; flex-direction: column; border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .city-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 160px 1fr; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); transition: background 0.2s; }
  .city-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .city-item:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .city-item--accent { background: rgba(200,240,84,0.03); }
  .city-name { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-primary); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; border-right: 1px solid var(--border); display: flex; align-items: center; }
  .city-item--accent .city-name { color: var(--accent); }
  .city-note { font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.6; color: var(--text-secondary); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; }

  /* Two col */
  .two-col { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1px; background: var(--border); border: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .info-card { background: var(--surface); padding: 1.5rem; transition: background 0.2s; }
  .info-card:hover { background: var(--surface-2); }
  .info-card-label { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .info-card-content { font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .info-card-content strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

  /* Tags */
  .tag-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.75rem; }
  .tag-row { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: center; }
  .tag-row-label { min-width: 80px; }
  .tag--muted { color: var(--text-muted); border-color: var(--border); }

  /* Connect */
  .connect-section {
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
    padding: 6rem 3rem;
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 4rem; align-items: center;
  }
  .connect-heading { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.2rem); line-height: 1.15; letter-spacing: -0.02em; }
  .connect-heading em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent); }
  .connect-sub { font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.75; color: var(--text-secondary); margin-top: 1rem; max-width: 440px; }
  .connect-links { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; align-items: flex-end; }
  .connect-link { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-secondary); transition: color 0.2s; }
  .connect-link:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .avatar-frame img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  object-position: center top;
}
</style>